I am so happy that people think that this DOLL is a real baby and that they are respectful enough to pray for it but please direct your prayers to the families of these babies. Society is cruel and unforgiving. Not only do they have to deal with the medical well being of their baby but they have to deal with the judgement of society and people that would have done different. If they could only mind their own business let them grieve and love their baby. If only they could see the beauty in difference and remove their opinion and stop projecting their reality on these parents. If only. I will always try my best to help represent every condition and I will always fight for the voiceless babies born with out a choice. I try my best to bring the most reasonable prices to parents for I know the price they are already paying. I study the conditions I sculpt for months  trying my best to represent them as respectfully  as possible. I know a small percentage will read this If at all and just jump to judgement but if you got this far thank you! I am just trying to help and show a Different perspective. Being different is beautiful and at the end of the day all we are all trying to do is live.

I’d like to show you the sweetness of nature. My cat TJ Loves my Dolls specifically this one. This is a doll with cranio facial duplication a condition that there are 38 cases of. For more information on the condition please visit my website linked in my Bio. I make these dolls because I think they are beautiful and I view them as just as worthy as any other doll because we are all unique and uniqueness dosent equate to life being less valuable. That’s my opinion.  I was watching a podcast from the inter-able YouTube couple Squirmy and Grubs talking about disability misconceptions and the one thing that really stood out for me is the misconception that people think that disabled peoples lives are “sad or depressing or inspirational” and you need to feel “sorry for them” or feel that they are less. People who are disabled are people just like you and me. They deserve respect and to be treated as anyone else you know and meet. When a pet meets a person who is disabled they will not wag their tail more or purr less because they are disabled they treat everyone as equal… I think that’s something humans should learn from nature treat people as equal no matter who they are. #dolls #babies #cute #cat
